The paper discusses the use of semantic information to improve iterative supervised learning algorithms, which falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on two algorithms, Geometric Semantic Genetic Programming (GSGP) and the Semantic Learning Machine (SLM), which are both used for regression tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed approach, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.SE (Software Engineering).
